[normal]Written evidence submitted by the UK Council on Deafness (UKCOD)[bold]About [bold]UKCOD[bold]UKCO
[normal]D is the UK's leading membership body for organisations concerned with Deafness. We provide access to specialist information, conferences and collaborative working 
[normal]opportunities, whilst providing a collective membership voice to political and cross sector partners.
[normal]Introduction [bold]Deaf people 
[normal]are 4 times more likely to be unemployed than the general population. The Job Centre Plus offer vital services that deaf people 
[normal]rely on. UKCOD feel that the accessibility of these services for deaf people could be improved in a number of ways. 
[normal]We use the term “deaf” to mean all deaf people, including those who use BSL, those who lipread and may wear hearing aids or cochlear implan
[normal]ts, and those who are deafblind.
